## Salt Bridge — example dom0 policy (reference only)
##
## The real /etc/qubes/policy.d/30-salt-bridge.policy is generated by
## dom0-install.sh from the positional arguments `<agent-vm> <target-vm>...`.
## It emits one `allow` line per (service × allowed-target-VM) pair and a
## catch-all `deny` for each service.
##
## This file is a reference showing the shape of the generated policy; it is
## NOT copied into place. Do not edit by hand — re-run dom0-install.sh to
## change the allowlist.
##
## Example: `bash sb-install.sh salt-bridge work dev` generates:

# --- saltbridge.VmList (no target argument) ---
saltbridge.VmList  *  salt-bridge  @adminvm  allow
saltbridge.VmList  *  @anyvm       @anyvm    deny

# --- saltbridge.VmStart ---
saltbridge.VmStart  +work  salt-bridge  @adminvm  allow
saltbridge.VmStart  +dev   salt-bridge  @adminvm  allow
saltbridge.VmStart  *  salt-bridge  @anyvm  deny
saltbridge.VmStart  *  @anyvm       @anyvm  deny

# ... identical per-target block for VmShutdown, VmNetworkInfo, VmExec,
#     VmExecRoot, VmReadFile, VmWriteFile, FirewallList, FirewallAdd,
#     FirewallRemove ...

# --- saltbridge.ConnectTcpPolicy (two-VM service; script enforces allowlist) ---
saltbridge.ConnectTcpPolicy  *  salt-bridge  @adminvm  allow
saltbridge.ConnectTcpPolicy  *  @anyvm       @anyvm    deny
